---
import Image from "astro/components/Image.astro";
import Faunakite from "../assets/images/faunakite.webp";
import GuanacoRental from "../assets/images/guanaco-rental.webp";
import BoletinOficial from "../assets/images/boletin-oficial.png";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Link from "../components/Link.astro";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";

const projects = [
  {
    image: {
      src: Faunakite,
      alt: "Fauna Kite home page",
    },
    title: "Fauna Kite",
    subtitle: "Kitesurf school app",
    description: [
      "Fauna Kite, a new kitesurf school with a tight budget, needed an online site to showcase services and enable student bookings for courses and classes. They were manually tracking info in Google Sheets via emails and calls, with no easy way to update content, events like kitecamps, or newsletters—creating inefficiency for a growing business.",
      "To keep costs low, I minimized development by using their existing Google Sheets as a free 'database' for bookings, automating data storage, email notifications (via free Nodemailer), QR code perks, and calendar events. For content like news and events, I chose Sanity CMS's free tier for its ready dashboard—avoiding custom CRUD builds, integrations with Sheets, or paid DBs, which cut workload and expenses while maintaining performance. Built with Astro for speed, deployed on Cloudflare's free tier.",
      "The site automated bookings and admin tasks, freeing the school to focus on teaching. It boosted visibility, engagement, and scalability without ongoing costs—designed with modularity so transitioning from Sheets to a real database would be straightforward as they grow. This turned constraints into a lean, effective solution that supports their expansion.",
    ],
    stack: [
      "Typescript",
      "Astro",
      "Google Sheets API",
      "Google Calendar API",
      "Gmail API",
      "React",
    ],
  },
  {
    image: {
      src: GuanacoRental,
      alt: "Guanaco Rental home page",
    },
    title: "Guanaco Rental",
    subtitle: "Rental app",
    description: [
      "Guanaco Rental, an audiovisual equipment business, was bogged down by manual processes: equipment lists shared via Google Sheets, bookings tracked in a makeshift sheet-based calendar, and reservations handled through scattered WhatsApp messages. This led to errors, delays, and no real-time visibility—admins couldn't quickly check availability, and clients had to wait for shared spreadsheets, making the whole operation inefficient and error-prone as the business grew.",
      "To digitize without overcomplicating, I built a single full-stack Next.js app with a customer-facing side for e-commerce-style browsing and real-time availability-based bookings—eliminating spreadsheet sharing—and an admin dashboard for centralized equipment management, including custom features like earnings splits based on ownership in their rental society, stock tracking, and availability. Why Next.js? It enabled seamless server-side rendering and API routes for both sides in one codebase, keeping development efficient. Additional admin tools included a proper calendar for orders, discounts, analytics, employee roles with permissions, and customer data insights. To handle legal requirements, I automated paperwork generation during bookings. The app was deployed on a VPS near Argentina to minimize latency for local users—balancing cost with performance in a region with variable internet.",
      "The platform transformed their operations, automating bookings, paperwork, and analytics—saving hours of manual work so they could focus on growth. Admins now easily track equipment status, customer reliability, and monthly performance, leading to better decisions. It even scaled seamlessly when they expanded to a new province, handling the added location without any system changes, proving the design's flexibility turned a fragmented mess into a scalable business engine.",
    ],
    stack: [
      "Typescript",
      "Nextjs",
      "PostgreSQL",
      "Prisma",
      "tRPC",
      "Tailwind",
      "Shadcn/ui",
    ],
  },
  {
    image: {
      src: BoletinOficial,
      alt: "Boletin Oficial home page",
    },
    title: "Boletin Oficial AI",
    subtitle: "Civic tech",
    description: [
      "In Argentina, the Boletín Oficial—a daily government gazette—publishes all national changes, from laws to administrative updates, amid rapid shifts under recent presidencies. Lawyers I spoke with relied on it to stay informed, but it's a dense, lengthy document filled with boilerplate like job postings that most people ignore. Citizens miss key insights buried in the jargon, lacking an easy way to access relevant updates without sifting through pages of irrelevant details.",
      "To make this accessible, I used Python's seamless PDF libraries to ingest the daily documents, then leveraged Gemini's 1M context window for AI analysis—extracting and categorizing key news into JSON format without bias. Why Gemini? Its large context handled full documents efficiently, focusing on relevance for everyday users rather than legal experts. The output feeds an Astro app for fast rendering, with a React-based AI chat embedding the day's paper in context for on-demand clarifications. This stack balanced automation (AI extraction) with interactivity (chat), keeping development lean while prioritizing neutrality and usability over opinionated content.",
      "The app delivers categorized, digestible summaries of government changes—like a neutral newspaper—empowering Argentinians to stay informed without the overwhelm. It saves time, fosters civic awareness, and highlights important shifts objectively, turning a bureaucratic resource into a public tool that's expanded users' understanding of national developments.",
    ],
    stack: ["Python", "OpenAI", "Gemini", "Astro", "React"],
  },
];

const experience = [
  {
    date: "July 2023 - Present",
    title: "Full Stack Developer",
    subtitle: "Strategic Architect for high-growth startups",
  },
  {
    date: "April 2023 - September 2023",
    title: "Wordpress Developer",
    subtitle: "Strategic Architect for high-growth startups",
  },
  {
    date: "2022 - 2023",
    title: "Full Stack Developer",
    subtitle: "Strategic Architect for high-growth startups",
  },
];
---

<Layout>
  <main class="font-sans">
    <section class="h-dvh px-4 lg:px-10 space-y-14 grid place-content-center">
      <div class="max-w-7xl font-display">
        <h1 class="font-bold text-5xl md:text-9xl uppercase">
          Building pragmatic web solutions
          <span class="text-blue-500">.</span>
        </h1>
      </div>

      <div
        class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-baseline md:justify-between gap-y-6"
      >
        <div class="text-lg md:text-2xl text-neutral-400 max-w-2xl">
          <p>Facundo Pellicer - Full Stack Developer.</p>
          <p>
            Building scalable systems where code solves real business problems.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex items-center gap-10 font-mono">
          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="text-xs md:text-sm text-neutral-500">FOCUS</p>
            <p class="text-sm md:text-base">Full Stack / AI</p>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-1">
            <p class="text-xs md:text-sm text-neutral-500">LOCATION</p>
            <p class="text-sm md:text-base">Remote / Global</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="py-30 md:py-40 bg-neutral-900 flex justify-center">
      <p
        class="text-xl text-center md:text-left px-8 md:px-0 md:text-4xl font-display max-w-5xl mx-auto text-balance"
      >
        My job isn't just to write code; it's to understand the underlying
        problem while keeping the big picture in mind.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section
      class="px-4 lg:px-10 space-y-40 md:space-y-60 py-30 md:py-40 mx-auto max-w-350"
    >
      {
        projects.map((project, index) => (
          <article
            x-data="{ activeTab: 0 }"
            class="flex flex-col gap-x-20 md:flex-row md:even:flex-row-reverse items-center"
          >
            <div class="flex-1 space-y-10">
              <div class="flex  items-center gap-4">
                <div>
                  <p class="text-blue-400 font-bold text-5xl md:text-7xl font-mono">
                    0{index + 1}
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p class="font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl uppercase font-display">
                    {project.title}
                  </p>
                  <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-neutral-400">
                    {project.subtitle}
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="relative z-20 flex-1 md:hidden block">
                <Image
                  src={project.image.src}
                  alt={project.image.alt}
                  width="600"
                  height="400"
                  class="w-full h-full object-cover rounded-md"
                />
              </div>

            <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 pb-4">
            <button
              @click="activeTab = 0"
              type="button"
              class="flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg uppercase font-semibold text-sm px-4 py-2 border border-blue-300 transition-colors"
              :class="activeTab === 0 ? 'bg-blue-300 text-black' : 'hover:bg-blue-300/10'"
            >
              <Icon name="circle-alert" class="size-6" />
              The Problem
            </button>
            <button
              @click="activeTab = 1"
              type="button"
              class="flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg uppercase font-semibold text-sm px-4 py-2 border border-blue-300 transition-colors"
              :class="activeTab === 1 ? 'bg-blue-300 text-black' : 'hover:bg-blue-300/10'"
            >
              <Icon name="lightbulb" class="size-6" />
              The Solution
            </button>
            <button
              @click="activeTab = 2"
              type="button"
              class="flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg uppercase font-semibold text-sm px-4 py-2 border border-blue-300 transition-colors"
              :class="activeTab === 2 ? 'bg-blue-300 text-black' : 'hover:bg-blue-300/10'"
            >
              <Icon name="trending-up" class="size-6" />
              The Impact
            </button>
          </div>

          {/* 
            THE FIX:
            1. We use standard class for static styles.
            2. We use :class for the dynamic logic.
            3. We inject the Astro variable ${pIndex} directly into the string.
          */}
          <div class="grid">
            {project.description.map((p, pIndex) => (
              <p
                class="text-lg text-pretty [grid-area:1/1] transition-opacity duration-300"
                :class={`activeTab === ${pIndex} ? 'opacity-100' : 'opacity-0 pointer-events-none'`}
              >
                {p}
              </p>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
                <ul class="flex items-center flex-wrap gap-2 md:gap-4">
                  {project.stack.map((tech) => (
                    <li class="px-4 py-1 bg-neutral-600 rounded-3xl uppercase text-xs">
                      {tech}
                    </li>
                  ))}
                </ul>
              </div>

            </div>


            <div class="relative z-20 flex-1 hidden md:block">
              <Image
                src={project.image.src}
                alt={project.image.alt}
                width="800"
                height="800"
                class="w-200 h-125 object-cover rounded-md"
              />
            </div>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </section>

    <section
      class="px-4 lg:px-10 mx-auto max-w-7xl py-30 md:py-40 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-y-20 justify-between items-center"
    >
      <div class="space-y-14">
        {
          experience.map((exp) => (
            <div class="space-y-3 border-l border-neutral-700 pl-10">
              <p class=" text-neutral-500 font-thin text-sm md:text-base">
                {exp.date}
              </p>
              <div class="space-y-1">
                <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold">{exp.title}</p>
                <p class="text-base md:text-lg text-neutral-400">
                  {exp.subtitle}
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-9 md:leading-11 text-pretty">
          I am driven by a <span class="text-blue-400">passion</span> for constant
          growth and <span class="text-blue-400">learning</span>. My background
          in sports instilled a <span class="text-blue-400">competitive</span> spirit
          that pushes me to improve every day. I also have a sharp eye for <span
            class="text-blue-400">details</span
          >. I believe sometimes the distinction between a good product and a
          great one often relies on the small things.
        </p>
        <p></p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="px-4 lg:px-10 py-30 md:py-40 space-y-20">
      <div class="flex justify-center">
        <p class="text-base md:text-xl text-neutral-400 tracking-widest">
          GET IN TOUCH
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="flex justify-center text-xl md:text-6xl font-bold underline underline-offset-8"
      >
        <Link class="relative z-20" href="mailto:facundopellicer4@gmail.com">
          facundopellicer4@gmail.com
        </Link>
      </div>

      <div
        class="pt-8 flex justify-center gap-14 items-center text-lg md:text-2xl"
      >
        <Link href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/facundopellicer/">
          LINKEDIN
        </Link>
        <Link href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/facundopellicer/">
          GITHUB
        </Link>
        <Link href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/facundopellicer/"> X </Link>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
